# ------- Opening -------

+1s say speaker="Lloyd McKenzie" text="All right everyone, let's get started. This is a special ballot reconciliation call for the R6 subscriptions content. We've got twenty-three tracker items to get through, so we're going to need to be efficient. Gino, you're driving the content today?"
+3s say speaker="Gino Canessa" text="Yep. I've got the list sorted by priority. I'd like to start with the ones that have the most implementation impact, then work through the editorial items at the end if we have time."
+2s say speaker="Lloyd McKenzie" text="Sounds good. Rick, you're scribing?"
+1s say speaker="Rick Geimer" text="Ready to go."
+2s say speaker="Lloyd McKenzie" text="And I want to remind everyone of the process — for each item, Gino will present the issue and proposed disposition. We'll discuss briefly, then vote. Dispositions are persuasive, not persuasive, or persuasive with mod. If there's a substantive change to normative content, that triggers a reballot requirement. Let's be mindful of that."

+2s chat id=chat-1 from="Gino Canessa" to="Everyone" text="Tracker items spreadsheet: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1example — sorted by priority column"
